---
title: Picker
---

p.-text Picker are used to select one or several options in a list.

h3 Base

h4 Type checkbox
p.-text
  | To render a checkbox picker, apply the class <code>a-input</code> to an <code>input type="checkbox"</code>
  |  inside a container with the class <code>a-picker</code>.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--4(style="background-color:#eee;border-radius:.15em .15em 0 0;")
    .a-picker
      each type in ['checkbox1','checkbox2','checkbox3','checkbox4','checkbox5']
        input(type="checkbox", class="a-input", id=`${type}`)
        label(for=`${type}`)
          = type
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-picker">
      <input class="a-input" type="checkbox" id="checkbox1">
      <label for="checkbox1">
        checkbox1
      </label>
      <input class="a-input" type="checkbox" id="checkbox2">
      <label for="checkbox2">
        checkbox2
      </label>
      <input class="a-input" type="checkbox" id="checkbox3">
      <label for="checkbox3">
        checkbox3
      </label>
      <input class="a-input" type="checkbox" id="checkbox4">
      <label for="checkbox4">
        checkbox4
      </label>
      <input class="a-input" type="checkbox" id="checkbox5">
      <label for="checkbox5">
        checkbox5
      </label>
    </div>

